Beijing: 中央民族大学出版社 / Zhong yang min zu da xue chu ban she, 2002.Biao, the easternmost of the Tai-Kadai languages, is spoken by the Biao people (标人) of Huaiji County (怀集县), Guangdong, China. The Shidong (诗洞) dialect is used. Liang considers Lakkia and Biao to be Kam-Sui languages (Liang 2002:159-160).Tones (Shidong 诗洞 dialect):1 = /55/2 = /214/3 = /54/4 = /132/5 = /35/6 = /22/7 = /55/8 = /35/9 = /12/10 = /22/
